body:
React v0.12.1

I have some SVG elements I would like to drag around. But the drag events do not seem to be working for them, although they work for other HTML elements. Click events are working fine on SVG elements, however.

In the following example, the `div` will print a SyntheticDragEvent to the console when you try to drag it, but the `circle` will not.

``` javascript
var App = React.createClass({
  handleDrag: function(e){
    console.log(e);
  },
  render: function(){
    return(
      <div>
        <div draggable="true" onDragStart={this.handleDrag}>test</div>
        <svg>
          <circle draggable="true" r="10" cx="20" cy="20" onDragStart={this.handleDrag} />
        </svg>        
      </div>
    );
  }
});
```

further, the parent `svg` will not fire an event either, even if you modify it as so:

``` javascript
var App = React.createClass({
  handleDrag: function(e){
    console.log(e);
  },
  render: function(){
    return(
      <div>
        <div draggable="true" onDragStart={this.handleDrag}>test</div>
        <svg draggable="true" onDragStart={this.handleDrag}>
          <circle  r="10" cx="20" cy="20"  />
        </svg>        
      </div>
    );
  }
});
```

In a perhaps unrelated issue, if you attempt to put an element into the `svg`, React will render it outside the `svg` anyway.

``` javascript
var App = React.createClass({
  handleDrag: function(e){
    console.log(e);
  },
  render: function(){
    return(
      <div>
        <div draggable="true" onDragStart={this.handleDrag}>test</div>
        <svg>
          <div draggable="true" onDragStart={this.handleDrag}>test 2</div>
          <circle  r="10" cx="20" cy="20"  />
        </svg>        
      </div>
    );
  }
});
```

renders:

``` html
<div>
  <div draggable="true">test</div>
  <svg></svg>
  <div draggable="true">test 2</div>
  <circle r="10" cx="20" cy="20" ></circle>
  <span>//</span>
  <svg></svg>
<div>
```

The 2nd `div` (test 2) is draggable here however
